Job Responsibilities: 

Handle corporate finance projects including IPOs, financial advisory on mergers and acquisitions, and / or related transactions;
Assist in preparing pitch books and executing transactions and conducting due diligence;
Prepare listing documents and draft announcements and circulars;
Liaise with other professional parties and communicate with relevant authorities, such as SFC and Hong Kong Stock Exchange in connection with respective execution of projects.

Job Requirements:

Degree holder in accounting, business, finance, legal or related discipline preferred
Professional qualification such as CPA and/or CFA are preferred;
Three years’ working experience in corporate finance or auditing, preferably with IPO Execution experience
Fresh graduates with relevant background are welcome
Proficiency in both written and spoken English and Chinese, fluency in Putonghua;
Strong analytical skills and problem solving capabilities;
Mature, responsible, independent and self-initiated;
Able to work under pressure, excellent communication and presentation skills

We offer attractive salary and 5-day workweek to the successful applicant. Please contact us by clicking 'Apply Now' or forward your full resume with present, expected salary and date available to career@ giraffecap.com for application.

Personal data will be used for recruitment purpose only.

(Applicants not contacted within 6 weeks should consider their application unsuccessful.)

Job Purpose

Responsible for the quality control, risk management and advice on the transactions of the Investment Banking Department.

Key Accountability

Assist the team leader to establish, maintain and review the internal control measures on Investment Banking Department;
Support the team leader on deal screening (i.e. DSC meeting) and ensure sufficient due diligence was done for IPO transactions (i.e. DDC meeting);
Identify and resolve the issues that the Investment Banking Department encountered in the daily operations to enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of the Department;
Strengthen the internal control systems by continuously refining the Procedural Manual and other work arrangements, etc.;
Promote the sense of and create a corporate culture of quality assurance, conscientiousness, risk and compliance;
Provide sound advice to Investment Banking Department to enhance the overall deal quality and facilitate transactions executed by Teams;
Review and comment on the submissions to regulatory authorities (i.e. prospectus, circular, announcement, reply letters, etc.) to improve the quality of submissions;
Liaise with regulatory authorities to facilities the execution of transactions.
Requirements
Master degree holder in Finance or related discipline(s) from a reputable university;
At Least 5 years work experience in reputable investment banks, Big4 accounting firms or law firms. Previous experience in HKEx or SFC is preferred;
Solid knowledge of regulatory requirements including the Listing Rules and the Takeovers Code;
Knowledge of the execution and operational procedures for different kinds of corporate finance;
Preferable with working experience in Chinese deals;
Attained all regulatory criteria for carrying out investment activities;
Good analytical, critical thinking, interpersonal and negotiation skills;
Ability to effectively prioritize and handle multiple tasks under tight deadline;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese including Putonghua.

Responsibilities
Provide support in Structured Finance project.
Assist the project execution work relating to execution of all Structured Finance projects;
Support in preparing business proposals.
Assist in any ad hoc duties as assigned
Skills & Requirements


Studying university degree in Accounting, Finance, Economics or related disciplines;
Proficiency in both written and spoken English and Chinese including Putonghua;
Self-motivated and a good team player;
Excellent communication, analytical and problem solving skill.



We offer competitive remuneration package and comprehensive fringe benefit to the right candidate. Interested parties please forward your full resume with availability, expected salary by pressing "Apply now".

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment related purposes only. Applicants not invited for an interview within 2 months from the date of this posting may consider their applications unsuccessful. Personal data will be destroyed after 3 months.

For further information about our Company, please visit our website: https://www.cmbi.com.hk/en-US/

Responsibilities:

Conduct/review internal control checks for projects such as independence, conflict of interest and anti-money laundering/sanctions checks;
Handle matters relating to Chinese Wall such as update of watch list and restricted list, and wall-crossing;
Responsible for updating, developing and enhancing compliance control policies, procedures, programs and monitoring their effective implementation;
Handle and monitor compliance review examination and maintain highest level of compliance standards;
Handle requests from group and headquarter and ensure smooth, accurate and timely communications;
Assist/conduct compliance investigation;
Prepare regular and ad hoc compliance management reports;
Provide staff training related to compliance guidelines and requirements;
Handle ad hoc projects and drafting and preparing reports and submissions.

Requirements:

Degree holder in Law, Accounting, Finance, Business Administration or related discipline;
A minimum of three-year compliance experience IBD/ECM/DCM;
Ability to identify issues and work independently and proactively;
High integrity and professional ethics;
Good organization and communication skills;
Strong analytical and presentation skills;
Self-motivated and a good team player;
Attention to details;
Proficiency in both written and spoken English and Chinese, fluency in Putonghua is a must; and
Immediate available is preferred.

We offer attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits to the right candidate. Interested applicants please send detailed resume stating present & expected salaries and date of availability.

(Data collected will be kept strictly confidential and used for recruitment purpose only.)

Responsibilities:


Involve in a wide range of international corporate finance transactions (including M&A, restructuring);
Fully participate in the financial and tax due diligence and the execution processes;
Play a key role in the investment project team;
Assist in preparation of accounting schedules for year-end audit;
Perform analytical and business analysis for management;
Handle ad hoc financial reports and projects

 Requirements:

Bachelor Degree in Accounting / Finance or an internationally recognized accounting qualification;
Minimum 4 years’ relevant experience, including 3 years experience gained in Big 4 / sizable listed companies;
Solid corporate finance experience in M&A transactions would be advantageous;
Working knowledge in the HK Listing Rules is required;
Excellent understanding of the PRC accounting rules and regulation;
Strong analytical, reporting and problem solving skills;
Result oriented and able to work under tight deadlines;
Self-motivated, responsible, a good team player and willing to travel;
Proficiency in computer application software;
Fluent communication skills in English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Immediate available is preferred.

*Candidates with less experience will be considered as Assistant Finance Manager.

We offer 5-day work, attractive salary package and other fringe benefits to the right candidate. 

Interested parties please send your detailed resume in MS Word format with your present and expected salary to us. 

All information received will be kept in strict confidence and will be treated only for employment related purpose.

岗位职责:

1. 负责区块链金融部内部各项工作的协助、跟进；

2. 协助项目渠道、运营、用户数据分析；

3. 关注行业趋势，整理分析行业现状及趋势，策划行业报告，竞品报告等;

4. 协助部门各项营销工作的执行及落地;

5. 协助区块链金融负责人完成其他市场相关工作。

任职资格:

1. 本科及以上学历，1年及以上工作经验（应届生需有实习经验）;

2. 书面英语优异，有海外留学背景优先；

3. 对市场营销有兴趣，区块链投资与项目运营经验者优先考虑；

4. 有项目跟进，执行的经验;

5. 有责任心，具备良好的逻辑思维能力及创意发散思维;

6. 具有良好的抗压能力; 扎实的文案撰写能力及优秀的ppt技能，熟练使用office办公软件。

Job Responsibilities:


Report to superiors under the hierarchy of Investment Banking Department adopted from time to time;
To assist in handling corporate finance assignments including IPO, M&A, financial advisory, compliance advisory and other fund raising activities;
To assist in performing data analysis, financial modeling and market data research works;
To assist in communicating and coordinating with clients and professional parties in the course of Transaction execution under the supervision of superiors in the Investment Banking Department;
To assist in coordinating and carrying out due diligence activities and documentation work;
To assist in preparing marketing materials, liaising with clients and to arrange meetings and perform other necessary works to assist the marketing team of the Investment Banking Department;
To assist in internal compliance work;
To provide such other assistance as requested by superiors, including deal origination supports.

Requirement:


Bachelor or higher degree holder with major in finance, preferably holder of a professional accounting or legal qualification and/or other related disciplines;
At least 1 year (2 years for associate) of experience in corporate finance, investment banking, other corporate finance-related fields ;
Independent, strong initiative and follow through, organized, conscientious efficient and works well under pressure;
Good computer skills including Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Chinese Word Processing;
Good interpersonal and communication skills;
Good command in both spoken and written English and Chinese including Putonghua;
Willing to undertake frequent travel and extended stay from time to time;
Any other duties as assigned by the Employer.
We offer attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits to the right candidate. Interested applicants please send detailed resume stating present & expected salaries and date of availability to Human Resources & Administration Department by email.

All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence and personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Establish and strengthen the relationships with financial institutions. Assist in formulating and implementing business strategies in achieving the business goals and sales targets of the bank. Implement marketing initiatives for commercial banking products for financial institution. Prepare credit proposal, perform comprehensive review and assessment of risks for all credit packages.

Requirements:

Degree holder in Business Administration or related disciplines;
At least 3 years relevant experience in credit analysis on financial institutions;
Passed in LE 1, 7, 8 or equivalent, IIQE (Paper 1, 2, 3 & 5) and MPF Intermediaries Examination is a must;
Substantial knowledge and exposure in commercial banking;
Aggressive, result-oriented with good business acumen;
Analytical with strong negotiation and presentation skills;
Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese, fluent in Putonghua is preferable.

(Candidate with more experience will be considered as Senior Relationship Manager.)

If you are flexible enough and zeal for a harmonious and supportive working environment where enables you to grow and succeed professionally, please send a full resume indicating your public examination results (HKCEE and HKALE / HKDSE), your present and expected salary and quoting reference number attention to Talent Acquisition Division, Nanyang Commercial Bank, 151 Des Voeux Road Central, Hong Kong or apply through email. For details, please visit https://www.ncb.com.hk/ and select the page Recruit.

We are an Equal Opportunities Employer. Data collected would be used for recruitment purposes only. Applicants who do not hear from us within 8 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and their data will be destroyed within 12 months of receipt.

Responsibilities:

Assist in handling full spectrum of company secretarial matters for the listed Group and its subsidiaries;
Arrange for filing of statutory forms and returns with registrars/regulatory authorities in accordance with relevant legal and compliance requirements as well as maintain/update secretarial records and registers;
Assist in organizing Board/Committee and Shareholders meetings and prepare meeting materials;
Assist in preparing of annual / interim reports, announcements and circulars;
Assist in ad hoc projects and other duties as assigned.


Requirements:

Degree or diploma holder in Business Administration/Corporate Governance or a related discipline;
2-3 years of working experience in handling company secretarial duties (fresh graduate will also be considered);
Good PC knowledge in MS Word, Excel, Powerpoint, and Chinese word processing;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese (including Mandarin);
Experience in listed company will be an advantage;
Independent, attentive to details, self-motivated with a strong sense of responsibility;
Immediate availability is preferred.

We offer an attractive remuneration package to qualified candidates who wish to advance their careers in a people-centered business. Interested parties please send your detailed resume with current & expected salary and availability.

For more information, please visit www.luenthai.com.

All applications will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for recruitment related purpose.

