Responsibilities:

Review quality of due diligence steps performed of IPO sponsorship projects including submissions on major matters to regulatory authorities and non-IPO sponsorship projects;
Identify issues of Listing Rule compliance, accounting matters and disclosure matters;
Review documents and record keeping of IPO sponsorship projects and non-IPO sponsorship projects, including prospectus, other listing documents, checklists and due diligence documents prepared by execution team; and
Provide compliance, accounting and other professional support to the execution team.

 Requirements:

 Professional qualification and/or university degree in Accounting or Finance is preferred;
At least 4 years solid experience in handling IPO and/or financial advisory transactions;
Work experience in regulatory body or sizeable firm is preferred;
Good knowledge in the Listing Rules, Takeovers Codes and regulatory requirements;
Good communication, analytical and problem solving skills;
Self-motivated, responsible and a good team player;
