The position is responsible for financial planning and analysis function at group level, providing insightful financial analysis to unlock the Group’s profit potentials.

Responsibilities include:

Lead annual budget, monthly and quarterly forecasts;
Evaluate business performance, identify issues and value added aspects;
Make insightful recommendation to support management decisions on the best use of resources;
Identify the key profit drivers and examine cost-efficiencies;
Produce analytic reports and develop financial models to monitor KPIs;
Provide recommendations on capital projects, analyse investment worthiness and risks;
Work closely with business units to measure and assess post-investment performance;
Keep tracking the effectiveness of business plans including use of working capital;
Continuous streamlining on existing work processes, react positively to changes;
Support ad hoc analytic assignments.

Qualifications required:

University graduate in Finance or Accounting and a qualified accountant or/and a CFA;
At least 8 years post qualification proven financial planning & analysis experience gained in sizable companies, Big 4 trained will be an advantage;
Strong interpersonal and communication skills with capability to interact with all levels of colleagues across different business units and corporate functions;
Ability to deal with multiple issues simultaneously and be active in problem solving;
Mature, organised, proactive, self-motivated, attentive to details while able to see the big picture;
Knowledge in Hyperion system and business intelligence tools will be an advantage;
Proficiency in Microsoft Office, expertise in preparing presentation decks;
Good command of English, Cantonese and Mandarin with capability to lead discussions;
Ability in preparing reports in Chinese.

We offer competitive salary, discretionary bonus, medical insurance, life and personal accident insurance, annual leave and staff purchase discount. Interested candidates please send your resume with salary expectation by email or clicking "Apply Now".

We are equal opportunities employer. Applicants who are not invited within 2 months may consider their application unsuccessful. All applicants may be considered for other suitable positions with DCH Group / CITIC Pacific Group and will be deleted from our files after 6 months from the date of application.

Responsibilities:

Work closely with Project Team to support overall project accounting throughout the project life-cycle, and take ownership in collecting and verifying data from various sources for cost reports;
Consolidate cost data for expenditures controlling, monitor project performance and participate in project review and control;
Analyze cost data and attend project reviews with Project Team to prepare management reports and business analysis;
Maintenance of the Project Master File including project initiation, project maintenance and change order management;
Act as a gatekeeper to project governance in accordance to statutory requirements, corporate policies and accounting standards;
Streamline complex procedures and support other ad-hoc projects as assigned.

 Requirements - Qualification:

Bachelor’s Degree in Finance/Accounting/ Business Administration;
Minimum 4 years of cost accounting experience at project levels, prior experience working in Engineering Consultancy and/ or project based companies would be an advantage;
Candidates with more experience would be considered as Senior Project Accountant; candidates with less experience would be considered as Assistant Project Accountant;
Proficient in Excel.

Requirements – Competences:

Good problem solving and presentation skills;
Able to work independently;
Diligent and proactive;
Numerical sensitive with analytical mindset and meticulous attention to detail.

We look forward to receiving your application with detailed resume stating working experience, academic and language qualifications, existing and EXPECTED SALARY as well as availability. All applications will be kept strictly confidential.

We offer promising professional career and exposure to right candidate, together with attractive remuneration package including discretionary bonus, continuing education allowance, medical and dental coverage.

Personal Data collected will be used for recruitment-related purposes only.

The applicant must possess

a recognised degree in legal / accounting / finance or other related discipline;
a minimum of 3 years’ post-qualification work experience, preferably in law enforcement or finance and accounting or quantity surveying duties;
experience in NGOs or handling levy reporting or law enforcement is an advantage;
track record in system implementation is a plus;
be proactive with strong critical mind to continuously improve levy operation;
high level of integrity and sense of responsibility;
excellent analytical, communication and leadership skills with detailed mind;
proficiency in Microsoft application software (including Word, Excel and PowerPoint, etc.) as well as Chinese word processing; and
good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese.
(Applicants who do not possess the required qualifications and / or experience may be considered for other positions within the organisation.)
Duties include

Report to the Manager – Finance, the incumbent is expected:

to perform levy inspection and prepare documents on potential offence cases;
to collect evidence, take statements for investigation of non-compliant cases and to serve as prosecution witness in legal proceedings;
to prepare and continuously improve reports to maintain strong corporate governance on levy;
to work with IT and other parties for system upgrade;
to handle levy related documents including levy forms, eForms, eServices accounts and web submissions;
to prepare levy assessment to contractors;
to follow up levy issues with contractors and authorized persons;
to answer enquiries from levy payers and relevant parties;
to perform data input and payment receipts in levy collection system; and
to carry out any other duties as assigned from time to time by the Executive Director.
Applications:
The position is on a renewable fixed-term contract (subject to performance and operational needs) for a period of 2 years. 
Please click the below “Apply Online” to complete the application form and upload the updated curriculum vitae, the results of English and Chinese Language obtained in public examinations, current and expected salary together with a covering letter stating one’s suitability for the job on or before 21 January 2022. 
For further details on CIC please refer to website: http://www.cic.hk.

Responsibilities

As the specific contact person of the department's external comprehensive affairs, specifically responsible for management and submission of all kinds of data statistics in IBD; responsible for IBD periodic summary and other working reports
Organization and implementation of comprehensive affairs of IBD, such as finance, compliance, and administration;
Supporting jobs in the back office of the investment banking, such as assisting in company research, collecting data, updating pitchbooks, etc.
Ad hoc tasks or projects assigned by supervisors
Requirements

Bachelor Degree, preferred in Business, Economic, Finance or related disciplines;
Mature, flexible, fast-paced and able to work independently;
Able to work under pressure and outside working hours to meet tight deadline, well-organized, responsible, self-motivated, willing to learn, detail-oriented with good interpersonal skill;
Strong communication skills and team work spirit;
Proficient in MS Office is required, familiar with Bloomberg, Wind and other database software are preferred;
Good command of spoken and written English, Mandarin and Cantonese. Ability to draft Chinese and English reports is essential.
We offer attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits to the right candidate. Interested applicants please send detailed resume stating present & expected salaries and date of availability to Human Resources Department by clicking "APPLY NOW".

